Sequencing Center: Korea Research Institute of Bioscience and Biotechnology
Comments: Candidatus Nitrosoterreus koreensis MY1 is ammonia oxidizing archaeon from rhizosphere.

Isolation Source: the muddy water of a sulfuric hot spring
Isolation Comments: isolated from the muddy water of a sulfuric hot spring in Yunnan province, China
Comments: This strain is new species of the genus Metallosphaera that was isolated from the muddy water of a sulfuric hot spring in Yunnan province, China.
